#compdef ldap-server-mock
# ============================================================================
# _ldap-server-mock — zsh completion for veo-labs's mock LDAP server
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/veo-labs/ldap-server-mock
#   Author     : Veo-Labs
#   License    : AGPL-3.0
#   Stars      : 66
#   Language   : TypeScript
#   npm        : ldap-server-mock v6.0.1
#   Binary     : ldap-server-mock  (package.json bin string → ./server.js,
#                                  npm registers as the package-name command)
#   Last push  : 2023-01-05
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   ldap-server-mock is "really simple basic mock for LDAP server" — a small
#   TypeScript Node.js server intended for testing client code that talks to
#   an LDAP backend, without spinning up a real OpenLDAP / Active Directory.
#   It loads two JSON config files at startup:  a "configuration" file
#   describing the bind port, the bind DN, the search base, and optional
#   TLS certificate paths;  and a "database" file containing an array of
#   `LdapUser` objects that become the server's directory contents.  Common
#   uses include SSO/auth integration tests in CI and offline development
#   against an LDAP-backed auth provider.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from server.ts getArguments() regex parser)
#   ldap-server-mock --conf=<FILE> --database=<FILE>
#
#   Both flags use the `--name=VALUE` long-equals form (the parser is a
#   custom regex `/--(conf|database)=(.*)/`;  separate-token long flags
#   are NOT accepted).
#
#   Required arguments:
#     --conf=<FILE>        Relative or absolute path to the server
#                          configuration file.  Loaded via require(), so
#                          .json / .js / .cjs are all accepted.  The file
#                          must export a LdapServerMockConfiguration:
#                            {
#                              port: number,            // bind port
#                              searchBase: string,      // LDAP base DN
#                              bindDN?: string,
#                              bindCredentials?: string,
#                              certPath?: string,       // TLS cert (optional)
#                              certKeyPath?: string,    // TLS key  (optional)
#                            }
#     --database=<FILE>    Relative or absolute path to the JSON file
#                          containing LDAP users.  Must export an array of
#                          LdapUser entries; each entry's fields become
#                          the attributes returned by the mock server in
#                          response to client searches.
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `ldapjs ^2.3.3` declared in package.json
#   `"dependencies"` block — the canonical Node.js LDAP v3 client + server
#   library (mcavage / ldapjs / node-ldapjs, 1625 stars).  Used in
#   `lib/server.ts` (`LdapServerMock` class) to bind a server socket,
#   listen for LDAP search / bind / compare requests, and respond from
#   the in-memory directory loaded from `--database`.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/veo-labs/ldap-server-mock/contents/package.json
#       → "ldapjs": "^2.3.3"
#   This entry is the TS-Node=114 leader bump that CLOSES Axis 59
#   (LDAP Directory Service Library) at 1/1/1 three-language symmetry:
#     Rust   = ldap3_proto 0.4  (R825, `yamldap`,  rvben    | kanidm/ldap3)
#     Go     = go-ldap/ldap/v3  (R826, `ldap2pg`,  dalibo)
#     TS-Node = ldapjs ^2.3.3   (R827, `ldap-server-mock`,  veo-labs)
#   Reaches the triple-114 landmark Rust=Go=TS-Node=114.
#
#   No completion for `ldap-server-mock` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.  Stock zsh
#   ships `_ldap` (for OpenLDAP CLI tools `ldapsearch` / `ldapadd` etc.)
#   but no `_ldap-server-mock`.
# ============================================================================

_ldap-server-mock() {
    _arguments -s \
        '--conf=-[path to the server configuration file (REQUIRED)]:conf file:_files -g "*.(json|js|cjs|ts)"' \
        '--database=-[path to the LDAP users JSON file (REQUIRED)]:database file:_files -g "*.json"'
}

_ldap-server-mock "$@"
